I reviewed the metric and log analysis: traces and error_logs were empty; orders.cpu shows a strong breach of its global P95 (max ≈4.53 vs P95 ≈2.61, ≈+73%) with the first exceedance at 2024-01-20 15:36:00 UTC, and orders.log.row_count has concurrent spikes at the same time. Other services show only minor or equality-to-P95 behavior. Therefore the most likely single root cause is a high CPU usage event on the orders service starting at ~15:36 UTC.

```json
{
    "1": {
        "root cause occurrence datetime": "2024-01-20 15:36:00",
        "root cause component": "orders",
        "root cause reason": "high CPU usage"
    }
}
```
